<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-12-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-12-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="950" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d950">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Eddy</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-12-26"><hi rend="italic">December 26,
                                    1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Eddy reports favorable news from Messrs. Gargiulo and Peet, the
                            committee sent to Djumabala, stating that they are in close touch with
                            brigands and will leave Salonica on December 27 for an unknown point on
                            the frontier, where a meeting with the most of the leading brigands will
                            take place. Mr. Eddy has every hope of their success.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>